TextBlock.TextLine: Antwerp 25 auy 1682
brussel ber nard vanden cloosten
mons in antwoort aen den ul van gisteren, en sijn de diche swaer bayen
noch niet gecomen, maer verwachte die alle daegen hebbende een schoone
sorteringe onderweyer, hebbe goede witte frisuerden maer geene roij alhoewel
binnen 8 a 10 doegen een pack engelse ray frilaeden sal hebben van
weste carsegen ben wel versien, waer het gaken dat ul set noodigh
hadde sal al sar wel dienen daer en tusshen verwacht tussen dit
en 14 daegen wel 25 packen met alle sorteringen, soo ul soo lange
can uyt stellen sal alles vers goet hebben nochtans ten present seer
wel versien, hebbe de vrijigheyt genomen van om op ul te bewijfen 9:300
te betaelen aen mons Joseps Sabberton ngevolgen een triefken hem
mede gegeven ift bij ul al dien het ue gelegen was al waer het bine
5 a 6 daegen ul sal mij vrint schap doen doch comt het ue niet
geleven soo gelief het te ontseggen waer in ick ul can dienen gelieft
te compranderen
brussel seger vander borght
Antwerp 25 aug i681
mons hebbe gosteren aen ul een blay laken gesonden per bode volgens
ordre, de welck niet en twijffele oft tis ul tot contensement geworden
hebbe alle packuijsen en winkels afgelogen ende niet eenen bay volgen
het stael ionen vinden, alleenelijck den medegaende lap van a
9½ can ul sich daer mede bedienen gelieft dat te doen men candr
noch doen toe verven, de sie willen die 16 stuyvers per a vercoopen
waer in ick ul can dienen gelieft mij liberlijck de conmandere
blijvende naer groetenisse
London Henry Maynaid
C 26 aug
mij last toyon was onsle 22 curtt with a bill for £100- onP. d. Cohere
for yd acctt sence non from you, so shall in large upon yd of 7h, I lave
given you creditt for my slare in the goods shipt, I could with they were
arrived, for I do much want every thing, I wonder of klercls stay
I beeng so backwards in tle GN. silver mareq feare will make mee a looser
of the customer. If you dave bought one bale of cottons more of 23 a 24d
please to proede one more assorted from 18 tot 22 sence butt non eeceding
22, for I finde that sort well bought renders best, though Icoffitt
cottons is butt small, yett wee must have itt, amonglst the spanish cloathes
desined please to provide 2 blews of the inclosed cullor one an ey lighter
then the other not acceding 6 p a y, nather under, if you have any spiculatin
of packuhites using, I would desire you to buy of each sort 10 p isteed
of 5 as last dosired, yett 5 of each to come f vere first, I doubt the worster
frises shall nott sell this yeare, as upon other yeares they did, wsoever to assort
them now by mee please to send 4 deune p. made up in 2 of a lovely drapcullon
not darcker, butt rather lighter then this
London Abram 7vian
C 26 aug 1682
Ick
mij last to yon was antle 19. cutt. sence recd. yd of 11d. I hope for Gods sake
that the bayes & kersies, & some cloathes of each sort will come by smith, or
ele wee au unden, by ydt waiting, you make mee feae the woist for smuch
is to saile by the curtt full or nott full & I lave now not bayes nor
cloathes resting that can serve mee neither any 30 yd heries, I can finde
no reason to complaine much of cotter, & I bonst know, why se should
not buy kerstes bederthen them wee least receaved: now I'll see, in the goods
naw to come what ience forward to do, I hope the light or white grayes
an made, & could with to have them here, for I should sell them, I cam
say nothing of the new man till I see the goods, butt they patt. do not promise
what you exspect, yett I shall be ver gledd weer wee can finde out the best
way, to proceed & continew in our trade, butt above all you must be expedient
& leave not the wae souse un assorted as now I am. I do expect to know
what passes with much opatiency, for I feare to loose my customers
I am Bartely sorry to see the packett n°. 10 seased, yett lope that you shall
be able to buy att for a small matter, of which I shall much long to
know the succed, as also of other concenner
dubln Elnatan Luim
C 26 aug
my last to you was on the 22: past jenee non fhom you, the laces you orde red
shall be ready this week, of wsich I shall send you the invoyce, oo the
meane iw bile n sole hath no order from you so accept my bill when fore
pray advise di the needfull, that when I draw my bill susters no dis grace
thare is no opprtunitie of shipping att ostend or Bruges for dublin, so shall
send itt in 2 packet by way of Rotterdam according to yd ord
Londen Joan Loyd
C 26d
I have a presty assortment of lace for you ready here which I Intinded to send
this post, butt iust now receave advise from dover that, one of themen wee imploy
there dath be rayed 27 pacquets with last post, so that I dar send non more
that way till further order of my correspondents whee fore slought good to
advise you this, that you please to give mee yd opinion, & f I shall send y
by long sea, or how. I have this day taken the lberte to draw on you
£114:1:4 t att 34.10 ats 2 use payable soshe ord. of m Henrij Willinghton
for which pray give due dnow. I am comised this week yds tykes, which
shall follow alsoe
